<script>
  window.postData = {}
  window.postData["new"] = [{"_id":"54196d3f97b2f83a1e00080a","id":"2014/09/17/meetup-12-year-anniversary-heiferman","title":"12 Years on, Meetup Still Envisions Powerful Communities","title_tag":null,"author":"James O'Brien","post_date":"2014-09-17T11:15:08+00:00","post_date_rfc":"Wed, 17 Sep 2014 11:15:08 +0000","sort_key":"1xudcw","link":"http://mashable.com/2014/09/17/meetup-12-year-anniversary-heiferman/","content":{"plain":"Think about all the change and growth Meetup has witnessed in the social-media space, since the company's birth in 2002. \n\nThat was the era of Friendster. One year later, in 2003, Meetup was just passing the 12-month mark when MySpace began its meteoric rise. The company had pulled together two years of connecting people by the time Facebook first appeared on Harvard University students' screens, and, in 2006, Meetup said hello to Twitter (but probably only in 140 characters or less).\n\nThe group-building and networking platform now boasts nearly 20 million members, according to Scott Heiferman, its co-founder and CEO. Approximately half a million events per month flow through its system, all of this managed by about 130 employees. \n\nThe point is, Meetup has survived where others haven't, and it's staked out a space all its own as a major, if somewhat atypical, player in the social-network milieu.\n\n\"Well, we existed before there was this current concept of social media,\" says Heiferman. \"And so, hot things will come and go, but we're going to outlive and outlast them all.\"\n\nSee also: Travel Planning App Gogobot Hand-Picks Which Events to Hit Up \n\nHowever, Meetup's mission is initially not \u2014 as Heiferman puts it \u2014 to overtake platforms such as Facebook, or beat the numbers of whatever metric one usually uses to define success as a business of its type. \n\nWhen it comes to its own future, what's clear is that Meetup has a mission particular to a very personal company vision. Meetup is about change for the better. It's going for a kind of cultural transformation.\n\nThe Humanist agenda: Meetup's metric means community\n\nUnlike the social-media rubric that suggests customers should spend as much time on a platform as possible, when Meetup works as intended the connections you create push you offline. To do what Meetup is designed to help you achieve, you have to walk away from the web and into the real-world \u2014 to go somewhere and interact with people, face to face. \n\nIt's not a phenomenon that Heiferman says worries Meetup's leadership. In fact, it's pretty much the point.\n\n\"It's too simplistic to say that we use the Internet to get people off the Internet,\" he says. \"It's important \u2014 it's essential \u2014 that they meet up offline, but, for us, we're in the business of building real communities. Our mission is that we want a world filled with real local communities.\"\n\nSo, perhaps set aside for a moment whatever concept of Internet-based metrics with which one is familiar \u2014 billions of users, or however many thousands of messages per second \u2014 Meetup is working on something else. Tangible or not, it's a humanist agenda, and it's fueled by what sounds like a sense of optimism about how we interact.\n\nHeiferman describes a Meetup group of moms based in Jersey City. \n\nThey require that their members attend frequently \u2014 they're after connections deeper than a typical list-serve might provide, the way he describes them. And then, when an individual needs something, from extra babysitting to a crib on short notice, the group's members dive into getting those resources into that person's hands.\n\n\"The magic that comes from the connections \u2026 this is really about getting people to collide, and to mesh together, and come together as friends,\" Heiferman says. \n\nSee also: The CEO of Meetup Does Not Have a Desk [VIDEO] \n\n\"The sharing economy is alive and biggest in these communities,\" he continues. \"Intricate, true, emerging communities that may not have existed if Meetup did not exist. That's where you get the hairs on the back of your neck stand up and you say, 'OK, we've got to make this greatest platform, and then we've got to make this better.'\"\n\nNext moves: Getting the offline world to meet \u2026 online\n\nMaking Meetup better, or bigger, or both \u2014 how Heiferman and his team go about doing that might, ironically, require the company to revisit its online iteration. \n\nBut ironic or not, Heiferman isn't kidding. He wants to see Meetup grow beyond 20 million users into something with even larger world-changing potential.\n\n\"The job of making people feel comfortable with other people,\" is one way that Heiferman describes an essential challenge that Meetup faces. Getting them to sign up, find groups, and take the potentially huge step of going to meet strangers for the first time: \"there's a lot to do there,\" he says.\n\nIt can sometimes seem impossible. When Heiferman hears about a meet-up supposed to support (say) cancer survivors in a nearby state, and he learns that there are not enough members joining to sustain that group, he talks about frustration. He says he wants to further bolster the speed and effectiveness with which Meetup's optimistic goals take root.\n\nAnd so, changes are underway. \n\nThe parts that Heiferman will talk about have to do with building out the social-media tools that Meetup members have at their disposal \u2014 adding ways to connect prior to, and then during, the platform's offline group lifecycle. \n\nWhile Meetup offers basic chat functions within its group pages, Heiferman suggests there are more steps to take when it comes to getting people together in the digital space. \n\n\"They meet up, which is amazing,\" he says, \"and they throw comments around, but we have an opportunity to \u2014 in a modern global world and in a modern global way \u2014 enable them to talk to each other online in addition to offline.\"\n\nThe plans aren\u2019t ready for a press release, yet, however. \n\n\"I can't reveal too much more than that,\" says Heiferman, \"because it's hinting too much at what's around the corner. But it's going to be a really big year for us.\"\n\nNo matter what the next move, 12 years into its quest for new ways to amplify human connections, Meetup has already got perseverance in its portfolio. Now, it just needs its community to catch up with the platform-makers' goals.\n\n\"To your point about longevity, look, the impossible takes a while,\" Heiferman says. \"We're doing something hard. We're trying to change culture, and that takes a while.\""},"shares":{"twitter":904,"facebook":197,"google_plus":16,"linked_in":72,"pinterest":1,"total":1190},"comments_count":0,"image":"http://rack.1.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE0LzA5LzE3L2IzL01lZXR1cC4xMGFhZS5wbmcKcAl0aHVtYgk5NTB4NTM0IwplCWpwZw/fbc69c20/ab8/Meetup.jpg","responsive_images":[{"image":"http://rack.1.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE0LzA5LzE3L2IzL01lZXR1cC4xMGFhZS5wbmcKcAl0aHVtYgkxNzV4MTc1IwplCWpwZw/c79653ee/ab8/Meetup.jpg","query":true,"size":"175x175#"},{"image":"http://rack.1.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE0LzA5LzE3L2IzL01lZXR1cC4xMGFhZS5wbmcKcAl0aHVtYgkzNTB4MzUwIwplCWpwZw/960151c6/ab8/Meetup.jpg","query":"(min-resolution: 1.5dppx)","size":"350x350#"},{"image":"http://rack.2.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE0LzA5LzE3L2IzL01lZXR1cC4xMGFhZS5wbmcKcAl0aHVtYgk4MHg4MCMKZQlqcGc/49fda626/ab8/Meetup.jpg","query":"(max-width: 480px)","size":"80x80#"},{"image":"http://rack.3.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE0LzA5LzE3L2IzL01lZXR1cC4xMGFhZS5wbmcKcAl0aHVtYgkxNjB4MTYwIwplCWpwZw/1efa5a32/ab8/Meetup.jpg","query":"(max-width: 480px) and (min-resolution: 1.5dppx)","size":"160x160#"}],"short_url":"http://on.mash.to/1BLLPk6","choice":false,"spotlight":false,"shortcode_data":{"see_also":[{"data-slug":"gogobot-activities"},{"data-slug":"scott-heiferman-meetup-video"}]},"excerpt":"Meetup has survived where others haven't, and it's staked out a space all its own as a major, if somewhat atypical, player in the social-network milieu.","sponsorship_footer":true,"channel":"Social Media","channel_link":"http://mashable.com/social-media/"},{"_id":"540f30c512d2cd282e002b1c","id":"2014/09/09/apple-live-hub-social","title":"Apple Finally Gets Social With Its Own 'Live Hub' for iPhone Event","title_tag":null,"author":"Christina Warren","post_date":"2014-09-09T16:54:20+00:00","post_date_rfc":"Tue, 09 Sep 2014 16:54:20 +0000","sort_key":"1xrpjN","link":"http://mashable.com/2014/09/09/apple-live-hub-social/","content":{"plain":"Want more proof that Tuesday's Apple event is a big deal? Even Apple is getting in on the fun.\n\nFor the first time, the company has rolled out a Pinterest-style social hub to accompany its live stream page at Apple.com/live.\n\nSee also: How to Watch Apple's iPhone 6 Live Stream\n\nIn addition to the live stream, Apple will be publishing photos, behind-the-scenes tidbits, play-by-play commentary and real-time reactions from attendees and the web. (Even the live stream itself is a rarity for an iPhone event.)\n\nPlus, Apple is getting social. The notoriously closed-off company has added share buttons to each tidbit on the page to allow easy posting to Facebook, Tumblr, Pinterest and Twitter, all under the hashtag #AppleLive.\n\nApple with its own hashtag? Times really are changing. And we like it!"},"shares":{"facebook":201,"twitter":977,"linked_in":71,"google_plus":16,"pinterest":1,"total":1266},"comments_count":0,"image":"http://rack.2.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE0LzA5LzA5LzYyL0FwcGxlR2V0c1NvLjliMzMxLmpwZwpwCXRodW1iCTk1MHg1MzQjCmUJanBn/3612908c/916/Apple-Gets-Social-01.jpg","responsive_images":[{"image":"http://rack.2.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE0LzA5LzA5LzYyL0FwcGxlR2V0c1NvLjliMzMxLmpwZwpwCXRodW1iCTE3NXgxNzUjCmUJanBn/8bd70ef0/916/Apple-Gets-Social-01.jpg","query":true,"size":"175x175#"},{"image":"http://rack.1.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE0LzA5LzA5LzYyL0FwcGxlR2V0c1NvLjliMzMxLmpwZwpwCXRodW1iCTM1MHgzNTAjCmUJanBn/adc7752d/916/Apple-Gets-Social-01.jpg","query":"(min-resolution: 1.5dppx)","size":"350x350#"},{"image":"http://rack.2.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE0LzA5LzA5LzYyL0FwcGxlR2V0c1NvLjliMzMxLmpwZwpwCXRodW1iCTgweDgwIwplCWpwZw/a2c13741/916/Apple-Gets-Social-01.jpg","query":"(max-width: 480px)","size":"80x80#"},{"image":"http://rack.1.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE0LzA5LzA5LzYyL0FwcGxlR2V0c1NvLjliMzMxLmpwZwpwCXRodW1iCTE2MHgxNjAjCmUJanBn/56843059/916/Apple-Gets-Social-01.jpg","query":"(max-width: 480px) and (min-resolution: 1.5dppx)","size":"160x160#"}],"short_url":"http://on.mash.to/1wbOwuV","choice":false,"spotlight":false,"shortcode_data":{"see_also":[{"data-url":"http://mashable.com/2014/09/09/how-to-watch-iphone-6-live-stream/"}]},"excerpt":"The notoriously closed-off company has put together a full #AppleLive social hub.","sponsorship_footer":true,"channel":"Social Media","channel_link":"http://mashable.com/social-media/","sponsored_by":"Apple Event","sponsored_by_url":"http://mashable.com/category/apple","show_sponsorship_in_new_col":true,"sponsor_utm":"?utm_cid=hp-s-e"},{"_id":"53ff81c3b589e45a08000688","id":"2014/08/28/mashies-late-entry-deadline","title":"Mashies Late-Entry Deadline Extended to September 5","title_tag":null,"author":"Marian Barrett","post_date":"2014-08-28T19:23:34+00:00","post_date_rfc":"Thu, 28 Aug 2014 19:23:34 +0000","sort_key":"1xn5ie","link":"http://mashable.com/2014/08/28/mashies-late-entry-deadline/","content":{"plain":"Last year's Mashies awards program saw the most creative Vine videos and GIFs to the most innovative uses of YouTube channels and branded content series. The bar was set high in 2013, but we are expecting this year's submissions to exceed expectations.\n\nWe are now accepting late-entry submissions until Friday, Sept. 5. \n\nCategories for this year's awards are expansive, including \u201cBest Branded App,\u201d \u201cBest Interactive Ad Execution,\u201d \u201cBest Social Media Campaign,\u201d among many others. Submissions will then be judged by a panel of experts within the industry, and winners will be announced at an awards ceremony in New York City. \n\nThe Mashies are Mashable\u2019s annual awards program recognizing the best in digital marketing, advertising and social throughout the year. The second annual awards ceremony will be held on Nov. 4 in New York City\u2019s historic Gotham Hall. \n\nMake sure you submit your entry by midnight on Friday, Sept. 5."},"shares":{"facebook":74,"twitter":636,"linked_in":432,"google_plus":7,"total":1149},"comments_count":0,"image":"http://rack.2.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE0LzA4LzI4LzY0L01hc2hpZXNsYXRlLjUzZTUzLmpwZwpwCXRodW1iCTk1MHg1MzQjCmUJanBn/3e39d383/df7/Mashies-late-entry.jpg","responsive_images":[{"image":"http://rack.0.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE0LzA4LzI4LzY0L01hc2hpZXNsYXRlLjUzZTUzLmpwZwpwCXRodW1iCTE3NXgxNzUjCmUJanBn/1fa727a7/df7/Mashies-late-entry.jpg","query":true,"size":"175x175#"},{"image":"http://rack.1.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE0LzA4LzI4LzY0L01hc2hpZXNsYXRlLjUzZTUzLmpwZwpwCXRodW1iCTM1MHgzNTAjCmUJanBn/016a6743/df7/Mashies-late-entry.jpg","query":"(min-resolution: 1.5dppx)","size":"350x350#"},{"image":"http://rack.1.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE0LzA4LzI4LzY0L01hc2hpZXNsYXRlLjUzZTUzLmpwZwpwCXRodW1iCTgweDgwIwplCWpwZw/f70acc03/df7/Mashies-late-entry.jpg","query":"(max-width: 480px)","size":"80x80#"},{"image":"http://rack.0.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE0LzA4LzI4LzY0L01hc2hpZXNsYXRlLjUzZTUzLmpwZwpwCXRodW1iCTE2MHgxNjAjCmUJanBn/29169783/df7/Mashies-late-entry.jpg","query":"(max-width: 480px) and (min-resolution: 1.5dppx)","size":"160x160#"}],"short_url":"http://on.mash.to/1oriVMW","choice":false,"spotlight":false,"shortcode_data":{},"excerpt":"Submit your best work in digital marketing, advertising and social to the Mashies by Friday, Sept. 5.","sponsorship_footer":true,"channel":"Business","channel_link":"http://mashable.com/business/"},{"_id":"53fca32db589e42bc900486c","id":"2014/08/26/how-to-get-a-job-using-social-media-class","title":"Learning How to Score a Job Using Social Media, for Beginners","title_tag":null,"author":"Sheffie Elencweig","post_date":"2014-08-26T15:09:15+00:00","post_date_rfc":"Tue, 26 Aug 2014 15:09:15 +0000","sort_key":"1xmin1","link":"http://mashable.com/2014/08/26/how-to-get-a-job-using-social-media-class/","content":{"plain":"With 92% of companies using social media in their hiring efforts, job seekers can\u2019t afford to overlook social as a vital resource in the job search. While you're busy job searching, employers are leveraging online resources to find candidates just like you.\n\nThat's why Mashable is collaborating with The Muse to bring you a free, email-based class series called How to Get a Job Using Social Media. The series features five different lessons with actionable tips on how to boost your job search strategy. Once you subscribe, content for the class will be delivered to your inbox each day.\r\n \r\nThese beginner-level classes will teach you how to establish your social brand, network with people online, identify career opportunities through social media, and turn leads into job offers. The classes include homework assignments to give you a head start in the process. Links to advanced readings will direct you to additional resources.\r\n \r\nYou can access the series here."},"shares":{"facebook":389,"twitter":901,"linked_in":448,"google_plus":38,"pinterest":4,"total":1780},"comments_count":0,"image":"http://rack.2.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE0LzA4LzI2LzI3L3Jzel84NTgzOTQ5LmE3NDUxLnBuZwpwCXRodW1iCTk1MHg1MzQjCmUJanBn/88082841/0f6/rsz_8583949219_d565d18edf_o_1.jpg","responsive_images":[{"image":"http://rack.2.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE0LzA4LzI2LzI3L3Jzel84NTgzOTQ5LmE3NDUxLnBuZwpwCXRodW1iCTE3NXgxNzUjCmUJanBn/8f8edc04/0f6/rsz_8583949219_d565d18edf_o_1.jpg","query":true,"size":"175x175#"},{"image":"http://rack.2.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE0LzA4LzI2LzI3L3Jzel84NTgzOTQ5LmE3NDUxLnBuZwpwCXRodW1iCTM1MHgzNTAjCmUJanBn/6f3a55c1/0f6/rsz_8583949219_d565d18edf_o_1.jpg","query":"(min-resolution: 1.5dppx)","size":"350x350#"},{"image":"http://rack.0.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE0LzA4LzI2LzI3L3Jzel84NTgzOTQ5LmE3NDUxLnBuZwpwCXRodW1iCTgweDgwIwplCWpwZw/6bc835b2/0f6/rsz_8583949219_d565d18edf_o_1.jpg","query":"(max-width: 480px)","size":"80x80#"},{"image":"http://rack.0.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE0LzA4LzI2LzI3L3Jzel84NTgzOTQ5LmE3NDUxLnBuZwpwCXRodW1iCTE2MHgxNjAjCmUJanBn/92000507/0f6/rsz_8583949219_d565d18edf_o_1.jpg","query":"(max-width: 480px) and (min-resolution: 1.5dppx)","size":"160x160#"}],"short_url":"http://on.mash.to/1wx1q7Z","choice":false,"spotlight":false,"shortcode_data":{},"excerpt":"Mashable is collaborating with The Muse to bring you a free, email-based class series called How to Get a Job Using Social Media.","sponsorship_footer":true,"channel":"Business","channel_link":"http://mashable.com/business/"},{"_id":"53fc98db12d2cd15f80058b7","id":"2014/08/26/social-good-summit-jimmy-carter","title":"Jimmy Carter Talks Preventable Disease at Social Good Summit 2014","title_tag":null,"author":"Marian Barrett","post_date":"2014-08-26T14:25:14+00:00","post_date_rfc":"Tue, 26 Aug 2014 14:25:14 +0000","sort_key":"1xmhGq","link":"http://mashable.com/2014/08/26/social-good-summit-jimmy-carter/","content":{"plain":"Former U.S. President Jimmy Carter will join the Social Good Summit this year via a special video message. Also the founder of The Carter Center, President Carter will speak about the ways social media is helping the eradication of six preventable diseases: guinea worm, river blindness, trachoma, schistosomiasis, lymphatic filariasis and malaria.\n\nFollowing the video message, two of Carter\u2019s advisory scientists will take to the stage for a one-on-one discussion. Dr. Donald Hopkins, vice president of health programs at The Carter Center and Dr. Mark Siddall, curator and principal investigator at the American Museum of Natural History, will delve into the possibilities of achieving eradication over the next 15 years and what that will mean for our world by 2030.\n\nThis new and innovative panel on global health will be one of many sessions looking at technology's power to better our world by the year 2030. Other confirmed speakers and panelists include Michael Dell, founder and CEO of Dell Inc., Liya Kebede, supermodel and maternal health advocate, Kweku Mandela, cofounder of Africa Rising and grandson of the late Nelson Mandela, and many more.\r\n \r\nThe Social Good Summit is a two-day conference about the intersection of technology and social good hosted by Mashable, the United Nations Foundation, the United Nations Development Programme, the Bill & Melinda Gates Foundation and the 92nd Street Y. The main event will be held at the 92nd Street Y in New York City on Sept. 21-22, and meetups will be held around the world.\n\nMake sure to buy your tickets to the event before they sell out!\n\nPurchase your tickets now.\r\nDate: September 21-22\r\nTime: Noon - 6 p.m. each day\r\nLocation: 92nd Street Y, 1395 Lexington Ave., New York, N.Y.\r\nTickets: $70 per day, or $110 for both days\r\nPress: Press credentials will be given to press and bloggers from around the world to the Digital Media Lounge (DML). The DML is a fully-wired workspace at the 92Y where you can report, network and organize interviews. Apply here.\n\nHave something to add to this story? Share it in the comments."},"shares":{"facebook":254,"twitter":891,"google_plus":9,"linked_in":55,"stumble_upon":202,"total":1411},"comments_count":0,"image":"http://rack.1.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE0LzA4LzI2L2Q1L3RpdGxlLjY0NDE0LmpwZwpwCXRodW1iCTk1MHg1MzQjCmUJanBn/ad1094f8/568/title.jpg","responsive_images":[{"image":"http://rack.1.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE0LzA4LzI2L2Q1L3RpdGxlLjY0NDE0LmpwZwpwCXRodW1iCTE3NXgxNzUjCmUJanBn/b6f42504/568/title.jpg","query":true,"size":"175x175#"},{"image":"http://rack.1.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE0LzA4LzI2L2Q1L3RpdGxlLjY0NDE0LmpwZwpwCXRodW1iCTM1MHgzNTAjCmUJanBn/6f2ca8ba/568/title.jpg","query":"(min-resolution: 1.5dppx)","size":"350x350#"},{"image":"http://rack.2.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE0LzA4LzI2L2Q1L3RpdGxlLjY0NDE0LmpwZ