nOn Sunday, Sept. 21 and Monday, Sept. 22, advocates from across the globe are coming together to discuss some of the biggest challenges our world is facing. Whether it's at local Meetups or at the main stage event at the 92nd Street Y in New York City, speakers will be initiating conversations about how our global community can start working today to help build a better future. \n\nSee also: In Anticipation of Social Good Summit 2014, a Look Back at 2013's Event\n\nWant to join the conversation but can't attend a Social Good Summit event? Don't worry -- here's how you can join the discussion online.\n\nLivestream\n\nIf you can't attend our main stage event in New York City, you can watch the entire Social Good Summit online through our Livestream. This year, the Livestream will be translated into seven different languages and broadcast around the world.\n\nAudio stream\n\nWith AudioNow, an audio broadcasting platform, listeners from all over the world can dial into Social Good Summit and tune into the latest discussions -- even without Internet access.\n\nUse the hashtag #2030NOW\n\nOur theme for Social Good Summit, #2030NOW, asks users around the globe, \"What type of world do you want to live in by the year 2030?\" In keeping with that theme, you can add your voice to the Social Good Summit conversation by using the hashtag #2030NOW on all of your social networks.\n\nMashable's social media coverage\n\nThis year, we will be live-posting quotes and scenes from the Social Good Summit to a variety of social platforms. You can follow along with our live tweets on Twitter at @socialgood, highlights from the summit on Twitter at @mashable, on Vine at Mashable Events and on Snapchat.\n\nTopi\n\nTo help make Social Good Summit as social as possible, we are launching our official event app on Topi. With Topi, you can access all the event materials, as well as interact and network with other participants. Here's how you can get started with Topi:\n\nDownload Topi on your mobile device (iOS and Android) from topi.com/get\r\nSign into the app via LinkedIn, Facebook or Google+\r\nOnce in the app, you will automatically access the event based on GPS location\r\nIf not at the event, or if before the event date, go to \"Info\" on iOS or \"Settings\" on Android, select \"Enter Code\" and input \"2030now\"\n\nWant a sneak peek of Social Good Summit?\n\nThis year at Social Good Summit, we are debuting the trailer for Beyond Right and Wrong, a new film about forgiveness. You can watch the trailer, below.\n\n Beyond Right & Wrong: Stories of Justice and Forgiveness - Public Trailer from Lekha Singh on Vimeo.\n\nPurchase Your Tickets to Social Good Summit\n\nThe Social Good Summit is where big ideas meet new media to create innovative solutions and is brought to you by Mashable, The 92nd Street Y, The United Nations Foundation, The United Nations Development Programme and The Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation. Held during UN Week, the Social Good Summit unites a dynamic community of global leaders to discuss a big idea: the power of innovative thinking and technology to solve our greatest challenges.\n\nDate: Sunday, Sept. 21 through Monday, Sept 22\r\nTime: 12:00 to 6:00 p.m. each day\r\nLocation: 92nd Street Y, 1395 Lexington Ave., New York, N.Y.\n\nPress: Press credentials will be given to press and bloggers from around the world for all Social Good Summit sessions and the Digital Media Lounge (DML). The DML is a fully wired workspace at 92Y to report out of, network with fellow members of the media and self-organize interviews and exclusive content from Social Good Summit sessions. The DML will be open from 9 a.m. to 6 p.m. each day. To apply, please fill in the form here.\n\nA special thanks to our sponsors Beyond Right and Wrong, the Jynwel Foundation, BT and the Caterpillar Foundation.\n\nHave something to add to this story? Share it in the comments."},"shares":{"twitter":1736,"facebook":776,"google_plus":138,"linked_in":801,"stumble_upon":545,"pinterest":1,"total":3997},"comments_count":0,"image":"http://rack.3.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE0LzA5LzIwLzdjL3NnczIwMTQxLmIxZmYzLmpwZwpwCXRodW1iCTk1MHg1MzQjCmUJanBn/197f69c3/7e9/sgs20141.jpg","responsive_images":[{"image":"http://rack.0.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE0LzA5LzIwLzdjL3NnczIwMTQxLmIxZmYzLmpwZwpwCXRodW1iCTM1NngyMDUjCmUJanBn/a13b471a/7e9/sgs20141.jpg","query":true,"size":"356x205#"},{"image":"http://rack.1.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE0LzA5LzIwLzdjL3NnczIwMTQxLmIxZmYzLmpwZwpwCXRodW1iCTcxMng0MTAjCmUJanBn/2255c290/7e9/sgs20141.jpg","query":"(min-resolution: 1.5dppx)","size":"712x410#"},{"image":"http://rack.1.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE0LzA5LzIwLzdjL3NnczIwMTQxLmIxZmYzLmpwZwpwCXRodW1iCTI4MHgxNTcjCmUJanBn/d33a6208/7e9/sgs20141.jpg","query":"(max-width: 480px)","size":"280x157#"},{"image":"http://rack.0.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE0LzA5LzIwLzdjL3NnczIwMTQxLmIxZmYzLmpwZwpwCXRodW1iCTU2MHgzMTQjCmUJanBn/bf24296d/7e9/sgs20141.jpg","query":"(max-width: 480px) and (min-resolution: 1.5dppx)","size":"560x314#"}],"short_url":"http://on.mash.to/XyD4KT","choice":false,"spotlight":false,"shortcode_data":{"see_also":[{"data-slug":"social-good-summit-2013"}],"wp_shortcode_manager":[{}]},"velocity":[966,962,955,948,957,965,973,978,982,984,985,986,998,1000,989,988,986,984,981,983,985,986,975,974,973,970,967,963,960,957,953,950,946,941,937,932,930,928,925,922,919,915,901,900,889,888,886,885,885,887],"show_sponsorship":true,"channel":"Social Media","channel_link":"http://mashable.com/social-media/"},{"_id":"541357edb05f9d5cfc00004a","id":"2014/09/12/off-the-page-vine-challenge-results","title":"6 Vines That Bring Stories and Doodles to Life","title_tag":null,"author":"Annie Park","post_date":"2014-09-12T20:30:31+00:00","post_date_rfc":"Fri, 12 Sep 2014 20:30:31 +0000","sort_key":"1xsy1M","link":"http://mashable.com/2014/09/12/off-the-page-vine-challenge-results/","content":{"plain":"Last week, we challenged you to give life to something on paper in a Vine. Canadian artist couple Daniel Lynds and Sundi Richard guest-hosted the contest, kicking it off with a few of their own examples.\n\n\"Something about the #OffThePage theme may have been a bit daunting at first, but after a few submissions, things picked up,\" they said. \"Ultimately we had a lot of fun and were blown away by the surprising interpretations of the theme.\"\n\nSee also: 8 Vines That Will Make Your Head Spin 360 Degrees\n\nLynds and Richard, a married couple that shares a film background, frequently collaborate on Vine to create live-action videos. They recently started a joint account as well. \n\nThe two are active participants in Mashable's Vine challenges. \"We love the diverse voices and the Vines that emerge from them,\" they said. \"And we enjoy waiting to see what will be submitted and the variety of ways the themes are interpreted.\" \n\nAbove all, Lynds and Richard appreciate the app's engaging and encouraging community.\n\nCurrently, they are working on running a local Vine festival called PEI Vine Fest in Prince Edward Island, Canada.\n\nTake a look at Lynds and Richard's favorite submissions, below. \n\n1. The adventure of alphabets\n\n2. Hospital workers in Africa\n\n3. Signing my contract\n\n4. Virginia Woolf\n\n5. Maria awakens\n\n6. The Little Prince\n\nHave something to add to this story? Share it in the comments."},"shares":{"facebook":159,"google_plus":29,"twitter":1079,"linked_in":78,"stumble_upon":871,"pinterest":1,"total":2217},"comments_count":0,"image":"http://rack.2.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE0LzA5LzEyLzlhL09mZl9UaGVfUGFnLmE5ODA2LmpwZwpwCXRodW1iCTk1MHg1MzQjCmUJanBn/bd764966/24e/Off_The_Page.jpg","responsive_images":[{"image":"http://rack.1.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE0LzA5LzEyLzlhL09mZl9UaGVfUGFnLmE5ODA2LmpwZwpwCXRodW1iCTM1NngyMDUjCmUJanBn/3a1ac1a6/24e/Off_The_Page.jpg","query":true,"size":"356x205#"},{"image":"http://rack.1.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE0LzA5LzEyLzlhL09mZl9UaGVfUGFnLmE5ODA2LmpwZwpwCXRodW1iCTcxMng0MTAjCmUJanBn/2c0a2ca1/24e/Off_The_Page.jpg","query":"(min-resolution: 1.5dppx)","size":"712x410#"},{"image":"http://rack.2.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE0LzA5LzEyLzlhL09mZl9UaGVfUGFnLmE5ODA2LmpwZwpwCXRodW1iCTI4MHgxNTcjCmUJanBn/496731db/24e/Off_The_Page.jpg","query":"(max-width: 480px)","size":"280x157#"},{"image":"http://rack.0.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE0LzA5LzEyLzlhL09mZl9UaGVfUGFnLmE5ODA2LmpwZwpwCXRodW1iCTU2MHgzMTQjCmUJanBn/0c18844e/24e/Off_The_Page.jpg","query":"(max-width: 480px) and (min-resolution: 1.5dppx)","size":"560x314#"}],"short_url":"http://on.mash.to/1oCr4iy","choice":false,"spotlight":false,"shortcode_data":{"see_also":[{"data-url":"http://mashable.com/2014/08/29/360-vine-challenge-results/"}],"wp_shortcode_manager":[{}]},"velocity":[865,855,846,837,828,819,810,800,791,790,781,765,756,747,738,730,721,712,704,687,679,670,661,653,644,636,627,620,612,606,599,593,587,581,574,568,562,556,550,544,538,532,520,515,503,498,493,487,482,477],"show_sponsorship":true,"channel":"Social Media","channel_link":"http://mashable.com/social-media/"},{"_id":"540f7f23b05f9d39ef003e0f","id":"2014/09/09/fashion-rocks-tweets-design-dress","title":"Verizon Turning Your 'Fashion Rocks' Tweets Into an Outfit","title_tag":null,"author":"Brian Anthony Hernandez","post_date":"2014-09-09T22:28:50+00:00","post_date_rfc":"Tue, 09 Sep 2014 22:28:50 +0000","sort_key":"1xrut8","link":"http://mashable.com/2014/09/09/fashion-rocks-tweets-design-dress/","content":{"plain":"A new type of eye-grabbing garment was created Tuesday night at the star-studded Fashion Rocks concert in New York City, where Verizon designed a fabric based on tweets during the telecast on CBS.  \n\nIt's a real-time garment, of sorts, with the online conversation about the night's music and fashion influencing the pattern and color of Verizon's final product. \n\nSee also: 50 Underwhelming Real Names of Famous Musicians\n\nParticipants had the chance to watch the #SocialImprint garment evolving on the backstage live stream, with each genre of music and certain fashion words changing the ultimate look.\n\nThe live stream displayed two screens detailing how the music buzz changed the color and how the fashion conversation influenced the pattern. A third screen, behind DJs Questlove and SoSuperSam, showed a digital model wearing the fabric.\n\nFashion Rocks at Brooklyn's Barclays Center featured performances from Jennifer Lopez, Usher, Nicki Minaj, KISS, Pitbull, Miranda Lambert, Jennifer Hudson, Luke Bryan, Enrique Iglesias, Duran Duran, The Band Perry, Rita Ora, Nico & Vinz, Afrojack and Magic. \n\nVerizon monitored the conversation every 30 seconds, accounting for unpredictable moments, too. After the broadcast, the telecom giant unveiled an interactive version of the final fabric, so participants could see which moments and conversations played a role in its creation. \n\nOnce the fabric was finalized and printed, Verizon announced a partnership Wednesday with Fashion Week designer Christian Siriano, who will put together the garment. \n\n (function(d, s, id) { var js, fjs = d.getElementsByTagName(s)[0]; if (d.getElementById(id)) return; js = d.createElement(s); js.id = id; js.src = \"//connect.facebook.net/en_US/all.js#xfbml=1\"; fjs.parentNode.insertBefore(js, fjs); }(document, 'script', 'facebook-jssdk'));\r\nPost by Christian Siriano.\n\nBONUS: 9 Fashionable Wearables for the Sartorially Savvy\n\nHave something to add to this story? Share it in the comments."},"shares":{"twitter":908,"facebook":226,"linked_in":79,"google_plus":24,"pinterest":3,"stumble_upon":190,"total":1430},"comments_count":0,"image":"http://rack.1.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE0LzA5LzExL2UzL3NvY2lhbGltcHJpLmExOTdmLmpwZwpwCXRodW1iCTk1MHg1MzQjCmUJanBn/04e39da7/7a2/social-imprint-verizon1.jpg","responsive_images":[{"image":"http://rack.3.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE0LzA5LzExL2UzL3NvY2lhbGltcHJpLmExOTdmLmpwZwpwCXRodW1iCTM1NngyMDUjCmUJanBn/a44ed6db/7a2/social-imprint-verizon1.jpg","query":true,"size":"356x205#"},{"image":"http://rack.2.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE0LzA5LzExL2UzL3NvY2lhbGltcHJ